## When to use
When you need an overview of your system's CPU resource utilization and want detailed statistics on each processor core.

## Approach
Utilize the `shell_exec` tool to execute the `mpstat` command, which provides comprehensive information about CPU activities. This approach allows for monitoring individual CPUs within a multi-core system, focusing specifically on CPU usage metrics like user time, system time, idle time, and other relevant statistics.

## Example
```sh
shell_exec "mpstat -P ALL"
```
This example uses the `shell_exec` tool to run a shell command that displays detailed statistics about each CPU core in the system.

## Pitfalls
- Ensure necessary utilities like `mpstat` are installed on your system.
- Be cautious about interpreting output correctly with complex multi-core architectures.